      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mesh refinement study with Richardson extrapolation and GCI < 5% on hemolysis index QoI; MRL 2 requires Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the impeller-volute domain (coarse 1.2 M, medium 3.1 M, fine 7.8 M cells). Richardson extrapolation was applied to the scalar shear-stress exposure integral used in the hemolysis power-law model. The observed order of convergence was p = 1.87 and the fine-grid GCI was 6.3%, marginally exceeding the 5% threshold. The team judged the shortfall acceptable given the monotonic convergence trend and the conservative nature of the hemolysis model, and the decision record reflects an Accepted outcome without formal deviation documentation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulation inputs within stated uncertainty bands; MRL 2 requires Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "All five operating points (2.5–5.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) were reproduced in simulation with inlet flow rate matched to ±2% and rotational speed to ±10 RPM. Blood analogue fluid viscosity and density matched to within published uncertainty of the Newtonian approximation. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared to experimental NIH within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty; MRL 2 requires Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values across all five operating points fall within the combined uncertainty envelope (simulation GCI + experimental measurement uncertainty). Maximum relative error is 8.1% at the highest flow-speed combination, within the acceptance band when expanded uncertainty is applied. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress exposure integral) are directly linked to the COU decision metric (RH < 1); MRL 2 requires Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed directly from the normalized index of hemolysis NIH, which is the primary QoI in both simulation and validation experiments. The shear-stress power-law model output maps monotonically to RH. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
