    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped out at MRL 2. The discretization error factor achieved a fine-grid GCI of 6.3% against a 5% threshold (Gradation 1 achieved, Gradation 2 required). The team accepted this marginal shortfall on the basis of monotonic convergence behavior and the conservative bias of the hemolysis power-law model, concluding that the overall credibility package is sufficient to support the COU decision at Medium assurance level. The claim supporting this decision was registered without explicit derivation provenance linkage, as the supporting evidence chain was considered self-evident from the validation result identifiers.",
